      "to_id": "cec50b17:25",
      "content": "Your orchestrator is cec50b17:0. Work inside `.synapse/worktrees/developer-25-eval-list-cap`. Commit your changes. Do not push.\n\nTwo changes:\n\n**Change 1 — src/db.ts: cap getAllEvalResults to last 20 tasks by task ID**\n\nFind `getAllEvalResults()`. Change the SQL query to only fetch eval results for the 20 most recent tasks (by task ID, not by eval timestamp). Use a subquery:\n\n```sql\nSELECT t.id as task_id, t.title, t.agent_id,\n       er.metric, er.passed, er.value, er.created_at\nFROM eval_results er\nJOIN tasks t ON t.id = er.task_id\nWHERE t.id IN (\n  SELECT DISTINCT task_id FROM eval_results\n  ORDER BY task_id DESC\n  LIMIT 20\n)\nORDER BY t.id DESC, er.metric\n```\n\nThis ensures we get the 20 most recently-evaluated tasks (by task ID descending), with their metrics, ordered by task ID descending.\n\n**Change 2 — public/app.js: render as a single unified list (no fail/pass split)**\n\nIn `renderEval()`, replace the current logic that splits into `failed`/`passed` arrays and renders two sections with a single unified list ordered by task ID descending (already the order from the API):\n\n```javascript\nconst rowsHtml = liveResults.map(r => {\n  const failedMetrics = r.metrics.filter(m => !m.passed);\n  return `<div class=\"eval-row ${r.pass ? 'eval-pass' : 'eval-fail'}\">\n    <div class=\"eval-row-header\">\n      <span class=\"eval-id\">#${r.task_id}</span>\n      <span class=\"eval-label ${r.pass ? 'good' : 'bad'}\">${r.pass ? 'PASS' : 'FAIL'}</span>\n      <span style=\"font-size:9px;color:var(--muted)\">${new Date(r.created_at).toLocaleTimeString([], {hour12:false})}</span>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"eval-title\">${esc(r.title.slice(0, 55))}</div>\n    ${failedMetrics.length ? `<div class=\"eval-failures\">${failedMetrics.map(m =>\n      `<span class=\"eval-chip\">${esc(m.metric)}=${m.value ?? '✗'}</span>`\n    ).join('')}</div>` : ''}\n  </div>`;\n}).join('');\n```\n\nReplace the `el.innerHTML` to use `rowsHtml` instead of separate `failedHtml`/`passedHtml` with section headers. Keep the metric counters bar and Proposals section.\n\nBuild `npm run build` and verify clean.\n",
